<a name="45-north-main"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Interstate 45 North of Downtown: Insufficient Lanes at North Main (Woodland Heights/Hollywood Cemetery)</div>

<div class="textblock">
    <div>
        From North Main to Loop 610 there is no right-of-way acquisition to appease the neighborhood group, even though the west side of the freeway has only low-grade commercial establishments and no homes.
This introduces a serious bottleneck where six northbound main lanes are reduced to four lanes at North Main. At evening rush hour, this will potentially cause a backup that will cascade into the downtown interchange complex.
    </div>
    <div>
        Let's remember that in 1992 Houston City Council members Sheila Jackson Lee and Jim Greenwood opposed the expansion of the West Loop, so the project was built with no new capacity added.
    Today, the West Loop is chronically congested at all hours of the day and at least 100,000 people every day sustain longer delays. What good has the lack of new capacity on the West Loop accomplished? <span class="bold">ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.</span>
        (Thank you Mrs. Jackson and Mr. Greenwood for sentencing West Loop motorists to additional delays every day.)
    </div>

    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Six northbound lanes reduced to only four lanes at North Main</li>
        <li>All lanes narrowed to 11 feet</li>
        <li>The bottleneck is exacerbated by the lack of access to the northbound managed lanes (see next issue)</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add at least one northbound main lane through the North Main intersection and all the way to Loop 610.</li>
        <li>Acquire a modest strip of right-of-way on the west side to accommodate the needed lane(s).</li>
        <li>Ideally there should also be a fifth southbound lane</li>
        <li>Have standard-width 12-foot-wide lanes</li>
    </ul>

        <div class="itemStatus">July 2015 Preliminary Status: Under Study</div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">HNTB says the performance of the proposed design is acceptable in the traffic model, but the extra northbound and southbound lane would have operational benefits. They are looking at pylon separation (instead of concrete barriers) and adjusting
        columns to determine if it is possible to add one or two more lanes under North Main. But since TxDOT set the ill-advised goal of not obtaining any right-of-way in this area, I would not be surpised if improvements are impossible.
    </div>


