<a name="allen-parkway"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Downtown Connector: Missing northbound access from Allen Parkway and no access to Memorial</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>There is a southbound exit to Allen Parkway, but no northbound on-ramp</li>
        <li>Allen Parkway traffic must make a detour to Bagby or Brazos to get on the connector, contributing to traffic congestion on those streets</li>
        <li>There are no connections to Memorial.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add a new ramp to the northbound connector to serve Allen Parkway</li>
        <li>Add two connection ramps at Memorial as shown on the map below</li>
    </ul>

    <div>Currently there are no connections at Memorial, but we need to think of the future. With increasing density and population along Buffalo Bayou and Washington Avenue, the Memorial connections will be needed to serve the growing population.</div>

    <div class="itemStatus">July 2015 Preliminary Status: Allen Parkway on-ramp will be added, no connections to Memorial</div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">For Allen Parkway, a loop connector similar to the currently existing loop on-ramp will be added to allow eastbound Allen Parkway traffic to get on the northbound downtown connector. 
        No connections will be provided between Memorial and the downtown connector. The City of Houston is against connections at Memorial, and TxDOT also wants to avoid connections due to space issues and complications introduced by ramps. As of July 2015, TxDOT is awaiting
        feedback from the City of Houston and the Downtown Management District about their preference for the Houston Avenue intersection. Design updates for this area are likely to be heavily influenced by the recommendation from the City of Houston and Downtown District.
    </div>
</div>

