<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>The merge and lane-switching zone from Elgin to Tuam is short and there will be heavy lane-switching</li>
        <li>The existing design is similar and suffers from poor performance</li>
        <li>If traffic stops on either connection (to I-45 north or to I-45 south), the other connection is adversely affected </li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Eliminate the merging/lane-switch zone by using braided ramps south of Elgin, separating traffic destined for northbound I-45 and southbound I-45.</li>
    </ul>

        <div>Separating traffic to prevent merging and lane switching is the principle which is used for the new Loop 610/US 290 interchange. That principle also needs to be applied here.</div>

        <div class="itemStatus">July 2015 Preliminary Status: Under study, changes possible if feasible</div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">
        HNTB agrees that it is desirable to eliminate this short lane-switching zone. There is a good chance this problem area will be fixed if a fix is technically feasible.
    </div>

</div>

