    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add a new westbound lane through downtown which connects to the downtown connector (southbound).</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="itemStatus">July 2015 Preliminary Status: Current design expected to remain as-is</div>
    <div class="itemStatusText">
        HNTB says there is low volume for the traffic movement from westbound I-10 into downtown. I agree with that, but that may not be the case 20, 40 or 60 years from now. I still think it is odd to have the connection ramp
        from the northbound downtown connector to eastbound I-10, but not from westbound I-10 to the connector. Obviously it was easy to add the ramp to eastbound I-10, but difficult from westbound I-10, so they decided to omit the
        ramp from westbound I-10 due to low volume.
    </div>
